metadata.name: torrent.ial #83
metadata.description:
Watch your image being created in front of your eyes

Variable length of drawing: between 150and 250 frames
5 different palettes: 50% chance for black and white (1) , 50% for color (4)
Variable density: 20% chance of some space between lines
Hardness: 20% chance for harsh strokes (if # of frames below 300)
Grain: 20% chance (bad luck?) of not having it
Rotation: 80% chance for top-bottom, 20% for left-right

metadata.name: Quantum Vacuum #543
metadata.description:
Empty space is not empty. It's filled with energy, transient fluctuations in quantum fields, bubbling with virtual particles popping in and out of existence. 

Part of an ongoing series of work combining my fascination with the fringes of fundamental physics, the emergence of complex behaviour through the interaction of very simple rules, and my obsession with hacking our perceptual systems. 

/Disclaimer: This is not a simulation, but an artistic conceptual interpretation and dramatization. :)

metadata.name: Wiggle #156
metadata.description:
Wiggle is a long-form generative collection of 1024 editions by Geoff Stearns that explores repetition using simple sine waves. There are 15 possible color palettes and the wave amplitude, complexity, and size are all variable.

The color palettes used in Wiggle are the same palettes used in Geoff's previous work, Hash Three Points (https://h3p.deconcept.com) and the projects share the same number of editions to invite collectors to find complimentary sets or pairs across the two projects.

https://twitter.com/tensafefrogs/status/1469491338714492929

metadata.name: Pinceau #155
metadata.description:
An examination of using generative brush strokes to emulate real life paintings.

The result of each output is determined by a number of factors:
- selection from 21 different palettes
- brush transparency levels
- scale factor 
- "chaos level" - determines how far off the given path any the brush strokes of any given piece decide to go.

More info and additional test mints can be found in this thread:

https://twitter.com/AndwerEric/status/1469083325881106440

metadata.name: Continuum #198
metadata.description:
This project is the culmination of many generative art experiments I have run throughout 2022. It relies heavily on the random walks through color and space techniques I have been working with, but also introduces other elements related to 2D and 3D rotation, framing and grains.

Continuum began as an abstract composition made up of a set of interacting elements against a background. This is still true. However, in my own mind, I have come to consider many Continuum pieces as peculiar, stylized observations of massive futuristic spacial, or quantum, constructions. Maybe even involving a wormhole through the fabric of space-time for some civilization well past 1 on the Kardashev scale. At the center is an erratic crystalline form, which is fed by power trains, and all around is a massive multicolored rotating containment structure.

Aside from the standard, inverse, threshold and washed types, the most defining trait of each composition is the “Back Style” which relates to a point of construction, activity or deconstruction of these structures. This is further refined by the panel style, the panel density and the rotation level. The other traits largely relate to color variability and aesthetics. 

This work has been coded using p5.js, and half of all royalties from the primary, and secondary, sales are assigned to the processing foundation.

Press s to download a 2400x2400 pixel image.
